Download and install netbeans: download.netbeans.org/netbeans/6.0/final/
Download and install git: git-scm.com/download
Download and install gitx: gitx.frim.nl

Set up ssh public key and register account at github.com: http://help.github.com/mac-key-setup/

Call the following from the terminal (once you add /usr/local/git/bin to your path):

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email your.email@whatever.com

mkdir columbia (or whatever you prefer)
cd columbia
git init
git remote add origin git@github.com:fwood/columbia.git
git pull origin master

After saving changes to files in the project:

git commit -a (be sure to write a comment! commit will abort otherwise)
git push

The Git Cheat Sheet: ktown.kde.org/~zrusin/git/git-cheat-sheet-medium.png